																				<div id="objectplayer" data-ooy="hwc293MzE6KVJiTQAOk9Jced879YZ6zU" data-autoplay="1" class="oovideo"></div>
											</div>
							
								
				
				
										
					<p>You can lose a lot of things being in business -- money, employees and the business itself. But if there's one thing you never want to lose, it's your edge, according to entrepreneurial expert <a>Patrick Bet-David</a>. </p><p>In this video, the financial adviser and Entrepreneur Network partner outlines ways to keep your edge in order to stay motivated and focused in rough times -- which of course will happen. </p><p>Bet-David says he's seen it all in his years in business -- good-looking, well spoken, talented, smart people with impressive backgrounds and college degrees -- but if those people don't have an edge, they're doomed.</p><p>"That edge is your energy," he says. "When your energy goes, everything goes... you've gotta be ready to have that energy and to come up with ideas."</p><p> for detailed shows notes and links mentioned in this video. </p><p><em>Watch more YouTube videos from <a>Bet-David on his channel.</a></em></p><p></p><p><em>The <a style="box-sizing: border-box; outline: 0px;">Entrepreneur Network</a> is a global movement of creative, energetic and inspired video creators sharing their ideas, experience and vision for the next generation of business founders and owners. We provide expertise and opportunities to accelerate brand growth and effectively monetize video and audio content distributed across all digital platforms for the business genre.</em></p><p><em> to become a part of this growing video network.</em></p>				
				
